  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators will conduct a prospective, single-center, randomized, double-blinded,
      controlled study to investigate the effect of early goal directed sedation on
      microcirculation in early septic shock patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Recent studies suggest that early goal directed sedation might improve the outcome of
      critically ill patients. The investigators will conduct a prospective, single-center,
      randomized, double-blinded, controlled study to investigate the effect of early goal directed
      sedation on microcirculation in early septic shock patients with relative stable
      hemodynamics.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
